The Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) Director, Dr John Nkengasong, says they have established a new COVID-19 information hub on the global health network in order to disseminate information for scientists, researchers and public health experts. Nkengasong addressed the Africa CDC weekly briefing on COVID-19 on Thursday morning. He says, “The global health network is a knowledge-sharing hub that facilitates the transfer of knowledge and exchanging methods, processes and research findings between regions.” Below is John Nkengasong’s full address: